<% var nameOfDocs = "docs-main5"; %>
    <script type="text/ng-template" id="/<%=nameOfDocs%>.html">
        <div class="wrapper toggled">
            <div id="sidebar-wrapper">
                <% var active = nameOfDocs %>
                    <% include docs-common-sidebar %>
            </div>
            <div id="page-content-wrapper">
                <div>
                    <% include docs-common-content %>
                </div>
                <h2>TILES Squares primitives</h2>
                <p>
                    The TILES toolkit enables the definition, implementation and manipulation of data type primitives. The TILES Square primitives
                    allow to abstract low-level implementation details into simple primitives for bridging the digital and
                    the physical world. The primitives are implemented in the fimware of the TILES Squares, and events containing
                    the identifier of the primitives will traverse the layers of the toolkit infrastructure upon interacting
                    with the Squares of an application. The TILES toolkit differentiate between two types of primitives:
                    <ol>
                        <li>input primitives - <i>originating from the TILES Squares</i></li>
                        <li>output primitives - <i>targeting the TILES Squares</i></li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
                <div class="docs-img">
                    <img src="/images/primitives.png" alt="primitives" />
                    <br/>
                    <span>RapIoT toolkit example primitives</span>
                </div>

                <p>
                    Example of primitives supported by the TILES Squares are listed in the tables below. In addition, the Squares features custom
                    ports to be used for extending the hardware Squares with primitives of your own design. To extend the
                    TILES Square primitives, see the <a href="{{extProcessUrl}}">Toolkit Extension Process</a>.
                    For a complete overview of all the currently supported interaction primitives, see the list of
                    <a href="/#/primitives">primitives</a> registered in the TILES Cloud web portal.
                </p>

                <table class="table table-striped docs-process-table">
                    <tr>
                        <td style="max-width:0;white-space:nowrap;"><b><i>INPUT PRIMITIVES:</i></b></td>
                        <td></td>
                        <td></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Primitive</th>
                        <th>Degrees of freedom</th>
                        <th>Example mapping</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Touch/Tap</td>
                        <td>Single, double</td>
                        <td>Send a command, log a quantity</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Tilt</td>
                        <td>Boolean (tilted/not tilted)</td>
                        <td>Select a function, binary switch</td>
                    </tr>


                    <tr>
                        <td style="max-width:0;white-space:nowrap;"><b><i>OUTPUT PRIMITIVES:</i></b></td>
                        <td></td>
                        <td></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Primitive</th>
                        <th>Degrees of freedom</th>
                        <th>Example mapping</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>LED feedback</td>
                        <td>Color, blink, fade <i>Supports hexadecimal representation of colors</i></td>
                        <td>Continuous notification about the status of process</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Haptic feedback</td>
                        <td>Vibration pattern <i>Supports long vibration and burs vibrations</i></td>
                        <td>Discrete notification about the status of process</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
    </script>